The Nigerian Supreme Council for Islamic Affairs, NSCIA,has condemned the killing of innocent lives and destruction of properties in Kaduna last week. NSCIA sympathizes and empathizes with those who lost loves ones in the crises. The Council uses this medium to express her most profound appreciation to the Inspector General of Police, IGP, for his swift response is sending a special investigation team headed by an AIG in charge of zone 7 to Kaduna to maintain calm in the troubled areas. The Council also appreciates the timely declaration of a dusk to dawn curfew in the State by the State Government. Tanimu is an Online Editor with Africa's Largest TV Network. Produces when not on Social media.